node.text: A Guide to Understand Your EMOTIONS pt. 2 #emotionalregulation #feelinglost #cptsd #allornothing #adhdprobs #adhd #neurodivergent #anxious #feelyourfeelings #depressed #feelingsad

@ninjaturtlebydefault IG doesn’t have a creator program right now 😭 but I mostly do videos because I want people to know the information that I wished I had when I was at my lowest or in times of confusion ❤️❤️ I’m glad they’re helping people!
@selfexperimenting  I appreciate you! These videos help more than you know.
Are you getting paid for this? Because you should be….🙌 thanks you so much for your support.
@sunshnemusic I’ll try to make a video on this for sure ❤️
Do you have a checklist or a daily practice system that can help bring more awareness and understanding? I guess a more practical way to actually implement these lessons? I find this super helpful

@selfexperimenting , Please do 🙏 I struggle with hope in reaching personal goals because I get afraid of making mistakes. You nailed it on the advice you gave about those who are overwhelmed. I get overwhelmed a lot and feel so much weight lifted off my shoulders when my boyfriend helps me. I'm grateful for the peace he brings me. I'll follow you to learn and practice how to bring peace to myself because I want to be more independent even while in a relationship 💝

Would a video like this for emotions like gratitude, hope, pride, satisfaction, relief, also help? Asking for those of us who may have trouble understanding all emotions, not just “challenging ones” …. Let me know! ❤️
@bethany_flamingo I do but I only have a couple of older episodes up. It’s on my list of goals this year to try to be more consistent with putting the episodes out ❤️
@preet.ttyyyy 🫠🫠 relatable honestly.. I’m gonna try to make more videos on how to identify what you’re feeling and how to allow yourself to feel it ❤️ you’re awesome friend!

@selfexperimenting yes please! I’m learning so much as I finally and painstakingly navigate an AudHD evaluation at 38 years old. This is a game changer for me. I’ve been so frustrated, reduced to tears because I feel broken that I can’t explain how I feel. This is very helpful. THANK YOU.
Most of the times either it's all of the or idk which one is it
@selfexperimenting Is this how our flirtation going to begin? 😉🫣
I just want to hug you! 🙌
@michii_moto ahh thank you! Make sure to give yourself most of the credit! You’re the one doing the work after all ❤️
Thank you for these videos! They are helping me start to better understand my emotions and myself 💖
@selfexperimenting lucky us. I swear you're helping me a lot ❤️ thank you ❤️
@holanatsumi thank you for being here friend ❤️
Thank you Sarah!! This is great stuff 😊
Thank you so much I really needed this
@ambitiouslyresilient I found it! It’s in Part 3, the video after this one. Thank you for these features!!!!!
@selfexperimenting Do you have a suggestion for Shame?
